reviews.text: The docents are amazing. Have a chat to one of the ladies and be amazed at their knowledge and enthusiasm. The museum has great displays and the info provided by the lovely Bernadette as we went to new sections made it an unforgettable experience.

Excellent modestly sized collection of artefacts telling the fascinating story of Cairns as we know it. Well thought through layout. Very nice building, clean light modern and airy. High quality research and tons of information - you could easily spend all day here if you read every piece. I particularly liked the effort put into multimedia displays. There were interactive computers, audio and visual as well as just written word. There is something for everyone's interest - natural history, ancient culture, modern culture, day to day life, medicine, law, society, art - the list is endless. The gift shop is brilliant and well priced too. A must-see, especially if you visit in the rainy season.
A must do for an any tourist interested in history. Will also recommend to Cairns locals as it tells the story of how Cairns grew to what it is now.
Great gor learning about the local history of Cairns. Lyn also explains it in Japanese if wanted.
Great place to learn about the Cairns region. Kids and adults will love it. And its air conditioned!!

We took our grandson here this morning and we all absolutely loved it. It was just the right size to occupy an active 5 year old for 2 hours. He loved seeing all the native animals especially Goliath the crocodile ! The staff were very friendly and informative.

Came up here only for taking a photo with Koalas.
That was extremely fun to see closely and hold them by arms, although it was over in a flash!!
I thought it'd better to spend more time to enjoy an activities and animals.
It was good when their was more animals at the dome. Still ok for tourist. More animals would be better.
Amazing place so much fun and quite a lot to do they have exhibitions every hour. Different levels of difficulty to suit everyone starting from easy to experienced.
My daughter enjoyed this place thoroughly. Went there on a rainy day. Don't miss hi-zoom

The food was 4 stars, and the service was 6! I was greeted with table service, with a big glass of ice cold water. They took my order within 5 minutes, and it was on the table 10-15 minutes later. I love how they also asked if I would like sauce with my chips, which is something I normally have to hunt down at many other places!

The burger I has was served on a fresh bun, with plenty of filling, but not so much that I couldn't squish it down and eat it normally. Not dry, and not too much sauce, perfect. The milkshake was also very good!

Would recommend

Very good burger, very nice staff. Did not like sitting on a sidewalk with people squeezing by and having to walk a block to use a public bathroom.  The food was good enough that I will take it carry out next time.

Had a bit of trouble deciding what to get as they're are so many options available. Once I made my choice, my taste buds were delighted. Table service was impeccable and staff were lovely. Drinks aplenty to choose from. See you soon cbc.
Stopped by for a quick lunch. Home made burger patties. Amazing!!! Washed down with the best chocolate malted thickshake in the north. Don't miss this little gem. 5 STARS
Burgers and chips spot on. Friendly and fast customer service. My 7yr old said it was the best dinner he has ever had.😃🤩
Beautiful meals great service. Definitely recommend it to everyone who is looking forward to a great meal in a very nice atmosphere. 5 stars easy.
Great place to chill on week days. Absolutely great service! Love to go again!
What a wonderful surprise, catered for a big table easily and the food was amazing. I ordered avocado on toast with goats cheese, it was honestly the best breakfast i have had in many years. Thank u.
Had the gluten free savoury buckwheat crepes and they were very good. Coffee was great also prices were OK and service was good.
Lovely  little suprise at the end of a lane way ..good food ..  good value ..good service ...lovely atmosphere..what more could you want ...cant wait to revisit  !

Delicious breakfast menu served 6.30am-3pm with some really interesting choices, and the staff were flexible if I wanted to add or take away anything. Breakfast cocktails served after 10am. 

Great for people watching while you eat. Centre of the city. Friendly and helpful staff.

Must try dinner too.

The seating is outside with an awning type covering the entire restaurant area. There are chairs and tables type seating and some bar and countertop seating along the street side. There is a full bar and wine menu. The regular menu is extensive with small dishes to a full meals and pizza. The prices are reasonable the dishes served were very good. The service was good. The restaurant is located in the center of the city.
Lovely little place. Menu was varied and staff attentive. Quieter location off the main strip of restaurants which is nice.

Hot day in cairns and was looking for some breakfast. Having walked past here many times I wanted to give this ago. Meals were great we had the Mexican eggs and French toast. Coffee in my opinion was ok, but not up to standard. That said I take my hat off to any place that still does a traditional Cappuccino. Worth giving ago as I'm basing this on 2 dishes. The service was also great.
Friendly staff and good looking menu! Great place to stop and cool off if you're adventuring around Cairns, or as a pit stop before or after a walk around the Gallery!
